    <h1 id="maincontent">Elementary School, Starting the Discussion</h1>
    <div style="width:300px; float:right; margin-right:10px; border:2px solid #772828; padding:10px">
      <h3 class="centered">Downloads</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/bullying/pdf/ele-starting-the-discussion-files/ele-supplimental-material.zip" target="_blank">Zip file of all PDF's and Supplemental materials listed below</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <p> A complete classroom tool kit for discussing bullying prevention. Features free downloads of daily activities, games and contests. </p>
    <p> <a href="#monday" target="_blank">Monday ~ An Overview of Bullying Prevention</a><br />
      <a href="#tuesday" target="_blank">Tuesday ~ When You See Bullying, What Can You Do?</a><br />
      <a href="#wednesday" target="_blank">Wednesday ~ If You Are Being Bullied, What Can You Do?</a><br />
      <a href="#thursday">Thursday ~ If You Are Bullying, What Can You Do?</a><br />
      <a href="#friday" target="_blank">Friday ~ Be a Kid Against Bullying</a> </p>
    
    <h3 class="hr"><a name="monday">Monday ~ An Overview of Bullying Prevention</a></h3>
    <p> <img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Introduce bullying prevention to students following the steps in the&nbsp;<a href="/bullying/classroom/elementary/ele-lesson-plan.asp" target="_blank"><strong>lesson plan</strong></a>&nbsp;that incorporates the <a href="http://www.PACERKidsAgainstBullying.org/kab" target="_blank"><strong>PACERKidsAgainstBullying</strong> <i class="fa fa-external-link" aria-hidden="true"></i> </a> website.</p>
    <p> <img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Distribute bullying prevention <a href="/bullying/resources/bookmarks.asp" target="_blank">bookmarks</a> to each student. </p>
    <p> <img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Introduce the three "<a href="/bullying/classroom/elementary/activities/stick-puppet.asp" target="_blank">Stick Puppet Plays.</a>" Set up the stage, create scenery, download the Club Crew members, color or download a color version, attach to craft sticks, and assign roles. </p>
    <p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Choose one or two of the <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/join-the-cause/class-projects/" target="_blank"><strong>Class Projects</strong></a> to do as a group. </p>
    <p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Use the <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/what-is-bullying/bullying-101-presentation/" target="_blank">Bullying 101 Presentation</a> to introduce young students to the basics of bullying prevention with familiar characters and student friendly language.</p>
    <p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Students often have a lot of questions about bullying, and some may be reluctant to share them with parents or teachers. <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/what-is-bullying/ask-carmen/" target="_blank">Ask Carmen</a> provides a safe outlet for kids to ask questions that are answered by staff from PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention Center.</p>
    <p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> It&rsquo;s really important for kids to feel that their voice is being heard. Through the Share Your Opinion features, kids have the opportunity to share their experiences with bullying in a simple, safe, and fun way: <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/what-is-bullying/share-your-opinion/" target="_blank">What Is Bullying?</a></p>
    <p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Give your students the chance to show off what they&rsquo;ve learned through an interactive quiz: <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/what-is-bullying/take-the-quiz/" target="_blank">What Is Bullying?</a></p>
    <p class="top"> <a href="#top">^ Back to Top ^</a> </p>
    
    <h3 class="hr"><a name="tuesday">Tuesday ~ When You See Bullying, What Can You Do??</a></h3>
    <p> <img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Ask students for their ideas on what they can do when they see bullying. Write down their ideas on 18x24 posters with the heading, <em>"When You See Bullying, What Can You Do?"</em> Display in the classroom. </p>
    <p> <img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Present the "<a href="/bullying/classroom/elementary/activities/scripts/LetMePlay.pdf" target="_blank">Let Me Play</a>" stick puppet play. Follow with post play activity and discussion. </p>
    <p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Review the information in the <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/how-can-you-help/if-you-see-bullying/" target="_blank"><strong>If You See Bullying section</strong></a><strong> </strong>of the PACERKidsAgainstBullying website.</p>
    <p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Have students complete the <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/are-you-a-target/" target="_blank"><strong>Are You a Target?</strong></a> and <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/do-you-bully/" target="_blank"><strong>Do You Bully?</strong></a> checklists. Ask them to complete both lists, explain that the more checks there are, the more likely it is that they are in a bullying situation.</p>
    <p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Let your students&rsquo; voices be heard by inviting them to share their insight with other students: <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/how-can-you-help/share-your-opinion/" target="_blank">How Can You Help?</a></p>
    <p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Even celebrities get bullied sometimes, and these <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/how-can-you-help/young-stars/" target="_blank">Young Stars</a> want to share their story with students to give them hope, encouragement, and inspiration. </p>
    <p class="top"> <a href="#top">^ Back to Top ^</a> </p>
   
    <h3 class="hr"><a name="wednesday">Wednesday ~ If You Are Being Bullied, What Can You Do?</a></h3>
    <p> <img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Ask students for their ideas on what they can do when they see bullying. Write down their ideas on 18x24 posters, with the heading, <em>"If You Are Being Bullied, What Can You Do?"</em> Display in the classroom. </p>
    <p> <img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Present the "<a href="/bullying/classroom/elementary/activities/scripts/Scrabble.pdf" target="_blank">Scrabble&reg;</a>" stick puppet play. Follow with post play activity and discussion. </p>
    <p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Review the information in the <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/are-you-a-target/if-you-are-a-target/" target="_blank"><strong>If You Are a Target</strong></a> section of the PACERKidsAgainstBullying website.</p>
<p> <img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Download the image of Pip (<a href="/bullying/classroom/elementary/activities/wheres-pip.asp" target="_blank">Where's Pip?</a>) and take pictures with Pip and students, which requires a camera OR students can draw a picture with Pip in it. Post the pictures in the classroom. </p>
<p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Let your students&rsquo; voices be heard by inviting them to share their insight with other students: <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/are-you-a-target/share-your-opinion/" target="_blank">Are You a Target?</a></p>
<p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Give your students the chance to show off what they&rsquo;ve learned through an interactive quiz: <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/are-you-a-target/take-the-quiz/" target="_blank">Are You a Target?</a></p>
    <p class="top"> <a href="#top">^ Back to Top ^</a> </p>
    
    <h3 class="hr"><a name="thursday">Thursday ~ If You Are Bullying, What Can You Do?</a></h3>
    <p> <img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Ask students for their ideas on what they can do when they see bullying. Write down their ideas on 18x24 posters, with the heading, <em>"If You Are Bullying, What Can You Do?"</em> Display in the classroom. </p>
    <p> <img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Present the "<a href="/bullying/classroom/elementary/activities/scripts/MasksScript.pdf" target="_blank">Masks</a>" stick puppet play. Follow with post play activity and discussion. </p>
    <p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Review the information in the <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/do-you-bully/if-you-are-bullying/" target="_blank"><strong>If You Are Bullying</strong></a> section of the PACERKidsAgainstBullying website.</p>
<p> <img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Create <a href="/bullying/classroom/elementary/activities/poster.asp" target="_blank">bullying prevention posters</a>. Display the posters in your classroom.</p>
<p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Let your students&rsquo; voices be heard by inviting them to share their insight with other students: <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/do-you-bully/share-your-opinion/" target="_blank">Do You Bully?</a></p>
<p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Give your students the chance to show off what they&rsquo;ve learned through an interactive quiz: <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/do-you-bully/take-the-quiz/" target="_blank">Do You Bully?</a></p>
    <p class="top"> <a href="#top">^ Back to Top ^</a> </p>
    
    <h3 class="hr"><a name="friday">Friday ~ Be a Kid Against Bullying</a></h3>
    <p> <img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Ask students for their ideas to prevent bullying in their school. What can students do, what can the teachers do, and other ideas. Write down their ideas on 18x24 posters, with the heading, <em>&#8220;Be a Kid Against Bullying.&#8221;</em> Display in the classroom. </p>
    <p> <img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Students can take the pledge to "<a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/how-can-you-help/take-the-pledge/" target="_blank">Be A Kid Against Bullying</a>"<br />
      <br />
      <strong>As a Kid Against Bullying, I Pledge To:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Speak up when I see bullying</li>
      <li>Reach out to others who are bullied</li>
      <li>And be a friend whenever I see bullying.</li>
    </ul>
    <p> Students taking the pledge receive the "<a href="/bullying/pdf/ele-starting-the-discussion-files/KABPledge.pdf" target="_blank">official certificate.</a>" <img border="0" src="/images/pdficon_small.gif" width="15" height="15" alt="pdf icon" /> </p>
    <p> <img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Meet the Club Crew. Visit the <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/what-is-bullying/learning-with-the-club-crew/" target="_blank">Club Crew page</a> to read and listen to their bios. Then select one or more of the members who they feel most connected with an answer these questions:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Which Club Crewmember did you choose?</li>
      <li>I feel connected to this crew member because _______________.</li>
      <li>How does this crew member feel about bullying?</li>
      <li>What advice would you give the Club Crew member about bullying?</li>
    </ul>
    <p> <img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Download the images of the Club Crew; <a href="/bullying/pdf/ele-starting-the-discussion-files/Brad.pdf" target="_blank">Brad</a>, <a href="/bullying/pdf/ele-starting-the-discussion-files/Carmen.pdf" target="_blank">Carmen</a>, <a href="/bullying/pdf/ele-starting-the-discussion-files/Chandra.pdf" target="_blank">Chandra</a>, <a href="/bullying/pdf/ele-starting-the-discussion-files/Jay.pdf" target="_blank">Jay</a>, <a href="/bullying/pdf/ele-starting-the-discussion-files/Matt.pdf" target="_blank">Matt</a>, <a href="/bullying/pdf/ele-starting-the-discussion-files/Mickey.pdf" target="_blank">Mickey</a>, <a href="/bullying/pdf/ele-starting-the-discussion-files/Molly.pdf" target="_blank">Molly</a>, <a href="/bullying/pdf/ele-starting-the-discussion-files/Mrs.%20Bridge.pdf" target="_blank">Mrs. Bridge</a>, <a href="/bullying/pdf/ele-starting-the-discussion-files/Nick.pdf" target="_blank">Nick</a>, <a href="/bullying/pdf/ele-starting-the-discussion-files/Pip.pdf" target="_blank">Pip</a>, <a href="/bullying/pdf/ele-starting-the-discussion-files/Sally.pdf" target="_blank">Sally</a> and <a href="/bullying/pdf/ele-starting-the-discussion-files/Shannon.pdf" target="_blank">Shannon</a>. Ask the students to color their favorite character and write down something that they learned during bullying prevention week. Display the posters in the classroom. </p>
    <p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Let your students&rsquo; voices be heard by inviting them to share their insight with other students: <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/join-the-cause/share-your-opinion/" target="_blank">Join the Cause</a>. </p>
    <p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Give your students the chance to show off what they&rsquo;ve learned through an interactive quiz: <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/how-can-you-help/take-the-quiz/" target="_blank">How Can You Help?</a></p>
    <p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Students are in the best position to tell us how bullying effects them, what actions from adults are helpful, and what they&rsquo;d like to see happen. You can give your students the opportunity to <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/how-can-you-help/share-your-story/" target="_blank">Share Their Story</a> with other students who may be facing similar challenges. The most important thing for students who are being bullied to know is that they are not alone.</p>
    <p><img border="0" src="/images/checkbox.gif" width="14" height="14" alt="checkbox" /> Answer the questions at <a href="http://www.pacerkidsagainstbullying.org/kab/what-is-bullying/did-you-know/" target="_blank">Did You Know?</a></p>
